        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 19 at 11:02PM MDT until August 20 at 12:30AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>SVRTFX

The National Weather Service in Great Falls has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Eastern Pondera County in north central Montana...
Southwestern Liberty County in north central Montana...
Southern Toole County in north central Montana...
East central Teton County in north central Montana...
Northwestern Chouteau County in north central Montana...

* Until 1230 AM MDT.

* At 1101 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 9 miles west of Lothair to 11 miles northwest of The
Knees to 11 miles east of Dutton, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters. At 1050 PM an Ambient Weather
Station in Brady mesured a 66 mph Wind Gust.


IMPACT...Expect considerable tree damage. Damage is likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

* Locations impacted include...
Shelby, Conrad, Dutton, Brady, The Knees, Lothair, Collins, Ledger,
Tiber Dam, Devon, Dunkirk, and Galata.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with these storms. Move indoors immediately. Lightning
is one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
